[h2 id=WhydoyourequireBittorrent?Can'tyoumakeapagewherethevideoscanbedownloadednormally? 
	" Why do you require Bittorrent? Can't you make a page where the videos can be downloaded normally?
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"Because regular downloads work like this:
	$LF
	[em 
		"Thousands of customers download from a single server
	]em
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It puts a lot of pressure towards that one poor server.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The uplink of this server is about 38 kB/s. Divide that by hundreds of
	$LF
	"customers, and you start seeing how "fast" you could download. I'd estimate
	$LF
	"about 0.1 kB/s. (And we're not yet talking about how long you
	$LF
	"would have to wait for the webserver to even answer your requests.)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Bittorrent works like this:
	$LF
	[em 
		"Thousands of customers download from each others
	]em
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It distributes the load.
	$LF
	[em 
		"If the number of clients grows, so does the amount of upload capacity.
	]em
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Download rates of 100 kB/s and greater are very well possible,
	$LF
	"because you download from all the fellows who are downloading
	$LF
	"the same file as you.
	$LF
	"Sometimes it's not that fast, because apparently not everyone wants
	$LF
	"to help the net to work. It's still faster than the "regular" way.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Trust me, this is the only option. Unless you want to buy
	$LF
	"me a 100 megabit internet connection.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Bittorrent is really cool. Your download rate is not limited
	$LF
	"by the server, because you're simultaneously downloading from
	$LF
	"all other clients of the same file.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But remember to return the favor - leave the download window
	$LF
	"open after your download is completed!
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"This is important for it to work!
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you are really helpful, read the chapter about 
	[a class=intlink href=/Helping 
		"seeding
	]a
	".
]div
